"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918386","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-12","<p>We have made no such assessment and all decisions on spending will be made at the Spending Review. The Government continues to work on the design and priorities of the UK Shared Prosperity Fund.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","150223 ; 150758","2018-06-12T12:45:37.61Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918386/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918386/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-06","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on regional development of the UK Shared Prosperity Fund being allocated using the Barnett Formula.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","150757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918387","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-14","<p>The performance of the Dartford Crossing is continually monitored. The design capacity of the Crossing is 135,000 vehicles per day. The average number of vehicles that used the Dartford Crossing per day in 2017 was 156,978.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-14T07:07:48.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918387/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918387/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-06","Dartford-Thurrock Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of trends in the number of vehicles using the Dartford Crossing; and to what extent that crossing is (a) meeting and (b) exceeding its operational capacity.","false","Biography information for Gareth Johnson","Dartford","Gareth Johnson","150644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918388","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-12","<p>We have made no such assessment and all decisions on spending will be made at the Spending Review. The Government continues to work on the design and priorities of the UK Shared Prosperity Fund.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","150223 ; 150757","2018-06-12T12:45:37.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918388/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918388/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-06","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what comparative assessment he has made of the level of funding planned to be allocated to Wales through the UK Shared Prosperity Fund and  European structural funding.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","150758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918389","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-12","<p>In April this year we updated the statutory Code of Practice for the Welfare of Dogs, made under the Animal Welfare Act 2006, which provides owners and keepers with information on how to meet the welfare needs of their dogs as required by the 2006 Act. The statutory code is available on GOV.UK.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-12T13:34:18.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918389/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918389/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-06","Dogs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has issued guidance to owners to encourage responsible dog ownership.","false","Biography information for Gareth Johnson","Dartford","Gareth Johnson","150645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918390","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-12","<p>We will create the UK Shared Prosperity Fund which will be designed to reduce inequalities between communities across our four nations as stated in the 2017 manifesto. The money that is spent will deliver sustainable, inclusive growth.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","150225","2018-06-12T12:43:37.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918390/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918390/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-06","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether the UK Shared Prosperity Fund will be directed in support of the priorities in the Industrial Strategy.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","150759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918391","Cabinet Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Electoral Commission is accountable to Parliament, via the Speaker’s Committee, and does not report directly to Ministers.</p><p> </p><p>In that context, the Government has not received advance copy of such a report, and would not normally expect to receive advance reports on its casework decisions.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-06-18T14:39:15.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918391/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918391/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-06-06","Vote Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Prime Minister's office has received an advance copy of the Electoral Commission's report into electoral fraud in the Vote Leave campaign; and what information he holds on the publication date of that report.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","150605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918392","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>The government recognises the importance of customs brokers in supporting business through the importing and exporting process.</p><p> </p><p>Future customs arrangements will depend on the outcome of the negotiations. In some scenarios, following the UK’s exit from the EU, we expect that there would need to be an increase in capacity in the customs broker sector to meet business needs.</p><p> </p><p>We are considering capacity and capability requirements for future customs arrangements as part of our EU exit planning.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-11T16:24:53.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918392/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918392/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-06","Customs Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he  has made of the number of customs brokers that would be required in the event that the UK leaves the EU (a) without a deal, (b) with a new customs partnership and (c) with a maximum facilitation agreement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","150606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918393","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>The government recognises the importance of customs brokers in supporting business through the importing and exporting process.</p><p> </p><p>Future customs arrangements will depend on the outcome of the negotiations. In some scenarios, following the UK’s exit from the EU, we expect that there would need to be an increase in capacity in the customs broker sector to meet business needs.</p><p> </p><p>We are considering capacity and capability requirements for future customs arrangements as part of our EU exit planning.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-11T16:27:27.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918393/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918393/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-06","Customs Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on (a) the economy and (b) revenue to the public purse of not recruiting an adequate number of customs brokers in the event that the UK leaves the EU (i) without a deal (ii) with a new customs partnership and (iii) with a maximum facilitation agreement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","150607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918394","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-11","<p>The Government remains committed to the Midland Metropolitan Hospital project. Ministers across Government are determined to finish construction as quickly as possible in a way that secures best value for the tax payer. We are in active discussions with all relevant parties to restart the project as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p>The lenders that finance the private finance initiative company put forward a proposal to restart the project. That would have involved a further contribution of public capital. Ministers concluded that this proposal was not acceptable to the Government, for a number of reasons, and that only a contractual solution could be considered.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-06-11T15:56:14.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918394/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918394/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-06","Hospitals: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 10 May 2018 to Question 139949, when work on the Midland Metropolitan Hospital is planned to restart.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","150571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918395","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-11","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-11T13:53:15.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918395/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918395/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918395/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-06","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2018 to Question 146881 on Personal Independence Payment, how many personal independence payment assessment reports (a) have included consideration of informal observations and (b) used those informal observations to come to a decision in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","150695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918396","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-11","<p>The Government is exploring a number of options to improve the provision of medical evidence for Personal Independence Payments and Employment and Support Allowance as set out in its response to recommendation 5 of the Work &amp; Pensions Select Committee.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201719/cmselect/cmworpen/986/98602.htm" target="_blank">https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201719/cmselect/cmworpen/986/98602.htm</a></p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-11T13:48:10.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918396/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918396/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918396/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-06","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the potential merits of collecting medical evidence from every applicant at the application stage of (a) personal independence payments and (b) employment support allowance.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","150696"
