"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918539","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-15","Based on the latest statistics, which relate to the end of June 2017, an estimated 73 per cent of ratings of known nationality employed by members of the UK Chamber of Shipping are non-EEA nationals. These figures are based on table SF0303 which was released as part of the ‘Seafarers in the UK Shipping Industry: 2017’ statistics.","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-06-15T07:58:18.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918539/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918539/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918539/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-06","Shipping: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to his Department's statistical release, Seafarers in the UK Shipping Industry: 2017, published on 30 May 2018, what proportion of Ratings jobs in the UK shipping industry are held by non-EEA nationals.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","150655"
