"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918578","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-11","<p>Broadcast and non-broadcast advertising are governed by a system of co-regulation and self-regulation respectively, overseen by the Advertising Standards Authority.</p><p> </p><p>The Advertising Standards Authority does not impose fines, but it can refer those advertising or promoting products to other bodies for the further action, such as Trading Standards.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-06-11T14:07:58.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918578/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918578/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918578/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-06","Infant Foods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what fines have been imposed on companies for promoting and marketing infant formula milk in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","150667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918579","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-11","<p>Where it is suspected that a death is as a result of homicide the coroner must consult with a chief of police on who should undertake the post-mortem. The Home Office maintains a register of suitably experienced and qualified forensic pathologists to conduct forensic post mortem examinations. The coroner will engage a pathologist from the register.</p><p> </p><p>Coroners have powers under the Coroners and Justice Act 2009 to ask a registered medical practitioner to undertake a post-mortem examination. The Coroners (Investigations) Regulations 2013 provide that the report must be made to the coroner as soon as practicable after the examination. I will raise the question of timeliness with the Department of Health and Social Care and will write to my honourable Friend.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","150551","2018-06-11T16:49:58.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918579/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918579/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918579/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-06","Post-mortems","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that when a coroner instructs a pathologist to carry out a post mortem examination to establish the cause of a person's death that examination is concluded within a reasonable time.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Sir Christopher Chope","150552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918580","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-11","<p>Having a personality disorder can have a big effect on the person's life, as well as their family and friends. We expect clinicians to use their professional training and judgement in diagnosing people with personality disorders and providing appropriate support and treatment thereafter.</p><p> </p><p>Treatment for personality disorders may involve talking therapy, group therapy and medication. Further advice and support is also available from the Royal College of Psychiatrists and the voluntary and charitable sector.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-06-11T13:24:25.57Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918580/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918580/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918580/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-06","Personality Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps are being taken better to diagnose people with narcissistic personality disorder and to provide such people with professional support.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Sir Christopher Chope","150553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918581","Home Office","false","2018-06-11","<p>The Northern Ireland Equality Commission has made a public statement on some of the advice given to Border Force, this is available at <a href="https://www.equalityni.org/Footer-Links/News/Employers-Service-Providers/Equality-Commission-Comment-on-Border-Force-Recrui" target="_blank">https://www.equalityni.org/Footer-Links/News/Employers-Service-Providers/Equality-Commission-Comment-on-Border-Force-Recrui</a></p><p>Furthermore in response to the answer to Question 140136 of 8 May 2018 the Minister of State for Immigration summarised the rest of the advice given.</p><p>These pieces of correspondence and advice are not routinely published, there are currently no plans to do so.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-11T16:42:15.363Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918581/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918581/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/918581/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-06","UK Border Force: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will place the advice given to his Department by the Equality Commission for Northern Ireland in respect of (a) the recruitment of Border Force officers and assistant officers and (b) applications from former members of the armed forces in the Library.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","150588"
